symbolic notations for statistical tablesand an approach towards automatic system design.wthe preparation of statistical tables is animportant function of the data processing systems of some organizations, and a symbolic notation for thedescription of tables has been shown to be a useful aid to documentation.  such a notation also providesthe first step towards making automatic a tedious and time-consuming part of system design and programmingin many computer applications.  one notation is described and suggestions are made for the implementation of the larger goal.cacm june, smith, b. w.ca jb march ,   : pm